#TSLLeadersInLuxury: The inaugural issue of The Style List: Top 50 Leaders in Luxury is here, and our cover stars are none other than the legendary duo Abu Jani Sandeep Khosla (@abujanisandeepkhosla).

These two unstoppable creative forces have paved the way for a brighter future in the country by establishing one of its most successful design labels. Iconic in their own right, Abu Jani (@abujani1) Sandeep Khosla (@sandeepkhosla ) have drawn inspiration from India and are celebrated for showcasing Indian heritage crafts to the world since 1986. After 39 years, they’re still making waves in global fashion and are the true definition of luxury leaders. 

Head to the link in bio to read their story and get your hands on the digital magazine!

#TheStyleListFestiveEdit is here, and we’re kicking off October with the excitement of India’s favorite season—Festive Season! From Diwali celebrations to dreamy Indian weddings and intimate family gatherings, it’s time for style, tradition, and unforgettable moments.

Our Festive & Wedding Edit is your ultimate guide for the months ahead! We’ve teamed up with fashion icons like Manish Malhotra, Ridhi Mehra, Abraham & Thakore, Dolly J, and Suneet Varma to bring you their best wardrobe tips. Stylist Esha Amiin (@eshaamiin1) also joins us, offering a dose of inspiration to elevate your festive looks.

Glow up with insider beauty secrets from top makeup artists, and let wedding expert Varun Tuli help you create the perfect wedding menu. Plus, our curated shopping guide is packed with festive must-haves—beauty, fashion, and home décor essentials to make your celebrations extra special. @akhand.official will surely delight your senses! And don’t miss East India’s first ever design show @design_milestone from 12-15 December! 

Get ready to embrace this festive season with style, elegance, and a sprinkle of luxury!

#TSLNews: This week, luxury is rewriting the rules—from beauty and fashion to travel and design. Huda Kattan buys back full ownership of Huda Beauty, making it one of the few founder-led beauty brands in the world. In fashion, it’s all happening—Dior names Jonathan Anderson as its new Creative Director, while Britney Spears x Balenciaga is the unexpected collab making headlines. 

Over in travel, Raffles Lakeshore Udaipur opens with signature elegance on the serene Udai Sagar Lake, and Ran Baas, The Palace is crowned one of the world’s most beautiful hotels by Prix Versailles 2025. Meanwhile in Paris, Le Bristol teams up with KRUG champagne for a summer kitchen pop-up. 

Back home, design takes a royal turn as Vikram Goyal Studio and Viya announce their debut showcase at the historic Burdwan Palace in Kolkata from June 18–21.
.
.
.
Scroll on for the entire scoop.

latestPosts.caption:
#TSLBeauty: When we think of going green, skincare isn’t usually the first thing that comes to mind — but maybe it should be. This #WorldEnvironmentDay, as we reflect on the choices we make that can help shape a healthier planet, it’s important to spotlight the quiet beauty evolution happening right here in India. Thanks to some of the world’s strictest cosmetic laws, Indian beauty labels have been nudged toward being more transparent, cruelty-free, and planet-conscious by default. Now, many are going a step further, creating formulas that are cleaner, smarter, and kinder to both skin and environment- a trend the west needs to pick up on. With roots in Ayurveda and eyes on global domination, these Indian brands are proving that beauty can be thoughtful — without compromising on results.

#TheStyleList #Beauty #CleanBeauty #Homegrown #MadeInIndia #Ayurveda

#TSLNews: Summer’s here, and Louis Vuitton is serving something sweet in the heart of Versilia! Say hello to the Maison’s very first seasonal ice cream shop, right outside their boutique in Forte dei Marmi. Inspired by the charm of Tuscan seaside towns, the gelato kiosk fits right in with its chic green tones and vintage market vibes—complete with Monogram flower details and a playful welcome from Vivienne, LV’s iconic mascot.

Every element—from the cups and napkins to the specially designed shopping bags—has been created just for this pop-up, with Louis Vuitton’s signature flair. Even the wafers come shaped like delicate flowers Serving artisanal Italian ice cream in collaboration with the iconic local gelateria Galliano, the kiosk offers ten classic flavours made with top-tier ingredients, alongside two exclusive creations: Vivienne, a creamy Portuguese milk gelato with a mandarin twist, and Gaston, inspired by the Tuscan dessert zuccotto, with sponge cake, crunchy bits, and dark chocolate chips.
Whether you’re savouring a scoop as you wander the stylish streets or picking up a tub for later, this gelateria is a little slice of Louis Vuitton’s art de vivre.

#TheStyleList #ForteDeiMarmiMoments #LVArtDeVivre
